    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "33a21d64_179a1fb3",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/eventbroker/BrokerApi.java",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 107,
      "author": {
        "id": 1006192
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T15:25:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This default implementation is creating a brand-new consumer for every existing consumer.\nIf I call this method twice with the same consumer, I\u0027ll get two different consumer instances.\n\nIs there any value in having this default implementation?\n\nIf not, why not just throw an `UnsupportedMethodException` instead?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 107,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 107,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "273162b6d5404474d678876c6b76ec7957d7a880",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "93cfb654_d1589810",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/eventbroker/BrokerApi.java",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 107,
      "author": {
        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T17:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason for adding these default implementations is to avoid forcing all existing brokers to adopt the new API in a big-bang change,  preserving the current behaviour for brokers that don\u0027t yet support message context.\n\nIf we were to throw an `UnsupportedOperationException` instead, existing broker implementations would still compile and deploy without issues, but would then fail at runtime as soon as someone uses the new methods (i.e. multi-site, websession-broker, pull-replication, and so forth).\n\nI think we should either require all brokers to implement the new API (and fail fast at compile time) or allow existing brokers to continue working unchanged, via the default implementations.\n\nI chose the latter, but we can discuss furhter.",
      "parentUuid": "33a21d64_179a1fb3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 107,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 107,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "273162b6d5404474d678876c6b76ec7957d7a880",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1f5ab588_63e6d61c",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/eventbroker/BrokerApi.java",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 107,
      "author": {
        "id": 1006192
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T22:54:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e The reason for adding these default implementations is to avoid forcing all existing brokers to adopt the new API in a big-bang change,  preserving the current behaviour for brokers that don\u0027t yet support message context.\n\nGotcha, but having a default implementation that throws an exception is still keeping the existing behaviour. The old brokers will just continue to support the old methods and not support the new ones.\n\n\u003e If we were to throw an `UnsupportedOperationException` instead, existing broker implementations would still compile and deploy without issues, but would then fail at runtime as soon as someone uses the new methods (i.e. multi-site, websession-broker, pull-replication, and so forth).\n\nThat is what I would expect: if a broker implementation doesn\u0027t support transactions, I would like to know it and not pretend they support them and discover that they are actually \"faking it\" using a default broken implementation at the interface level.\n\nI prefer failure to misbehavior.\n\n\u003e I think we should either require all brokers to implement the new API (and fail fast at compile time)\n\nThat would be even better IMHO: just avoid any default implementation and let them fail for the new one.\n\nSee the approach we have taken when we had to do the same with global-refdb (see https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/c/modules/global-refdb/+/390537) and a stepwise approach:\n\n1. Introduced an extended interface, keeping the current one\n2. Added the new methods to the extended interface (not all existing brokers will implement it)\n3. Deprecated the old one\n4. Remove the old one",
      "parentUuid": "93cfb654_d1589810",
