      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 1006192
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T15:25:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is quite big actually: if anyone is using this interface (e.g. multi-site) how does he know *IF* the runtime implementation of this interface will be thread-safe or not?\n\nI believe we should be stricter if we have evidence that common brokers have this limitation.\n\nI see two options:\n\n1. Just documenting it in a stricter way\n2. Documenting *and* checking it",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "273162b6d5404474d678876c6b76ec7957d7a880",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6349c298_d3e64d6b",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/eventbroker/MessageContext.java",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 39,
      "author": {
        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-02-24T17:54:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was mainly focusing on kafka, which is documented [1] to be NOT thread-safe.\n\nBy looking at Gcloud-pubsub docs [2] I read:\n\n```\n // This {@code MessageReceiver} passes all messages to a BlockingQueue. This method can\n // be called concurrently from multiple threads, so it is important that the queue be\n // thread-safe.\n ```\n \nSo it looks to be thread-safety has to be guaranteed explicitly by us.\n\nFor Kinesis, we have committing the offset` \u003d\u003d calling checkpoint using the checkpointer (we already do this at [3], from the same thread).\n\nThey do not (in the public docs) guarantee that the checkpointer itself is thread-safe to call from arbitrary threads. I can check the source code.\n\nI haven\u0027t checked eiffel, rabbitmq and nats implementation.\n\nBottom line is that thread-safety depends on the implementation (and the most common one do not guarantee it).\n\nI think documenting that implementations should take care of thread-safety is enough for the events-broker API, WDYT?\n\n[1] https://kafka.apache.org/25/javadoc/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer.html\n\n[2] https://docs.cloud.google.com/java/docs/reference/google-cloud-pubsub/latest/com.google.cloud.pubsub.v1.MessageReceiver\n\n[3] https://github.com/GerritForge/events-aws-kinesis/blob/refs/heads/master/src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/kinesis/KinesisRecordProcessor.java#L90",
      "parentUuid": "40ae1ddd_1d56f849",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 39,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "273162b6d5404474d678876c6b76ec7957d7a880",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
